Abstract:
Transcription of tradiitional vaihoho by Senhor Valentim, from Senhor Inacio da Conceiçāo.  The language is high, ritual Fataluku.

_0003 'En iharala vaihoho' is about traditional marriage and 'Hini vaihoho' is an orphan's lament;  
_0004 'En orontafan i vaihoho' is about husking rice;  
_0005 and _0006 'Ete seilana (Ete seilen) Leuli vaihoho' is about hauling logs from the forest, that will be used to make a traditional house (Uma Lulik);
_0007 'Txele Sipilen vaihoho' about harvesting corn together, call and response in conjunction with _0008;
_0008 'Txele Sipilana vaihoho' response to _0007.
_0009 'Aletielen Leuli vaihoho' about rice harvesting
_0010 and _0011 call and response vaihoho
